I've been obsessed with how even strangers destined to remain unknown can impact our lives. I'm currently in Piedmont Italy, where the rain has been constant. Yesterday, I saw a woman in a fluffy white robe, under a sun umbrella in the downpour, balancing a hot tea and a book in her lap, unaffected by the rain. Something in me said, do that right now. So I sat down under the useless, dripping umbrella in a robe, too. Felt the rain on my skin Natasha Beddingfield-style. Watched the misty rolling hills. It was a moment of tranquility, peace, and wonder I haven’t felt in weeks. Sending a thank you into the ether to the Piedmont Stranger. I love that we were never meant to say a word to one another, and your presence still positively affected me. Who knows!!! Maybe another white robe plunged into the rain, too.

I saw 2023 as a tough year. In many ways it was, but there was so much good too. I was looking through videos and it helped me see the good— it was an unintentional exercise in gratitude. The theme is meaningful connection, honestly. The good was in moments of connection to nature, friends, family,  resonant work, my partner and with myself. More of that in 2024.
